I'll be brief about this, as you can really only write rather silly
scripts for @dfn{KRSNAke} anyway.

@ftable @code
@item UP
tells the snake to move upwards
@item DOWN
what you'd expect
@item LEFT
ditto
@item RIGHT
ditto
@item QUIT
exits KRSNAke
@item NEWGAME
starts a new game if no game is playing
@item VERSION
returns the version string
@item HIDE
hides KRSNAke
@item SHOW
shows KRSNAke
@item WAIT FOR n
waits n snake moves
@item WAIT UNTIL X n
wait until snake reaches x position n
@item WAIT UNTIL Y n
wait until snake reaches y position n
@item SET SPEED n
sets the speed to n
@item GET LENGTH
returns the snake's length
@item GET PLAYING
returns 1 if a game is playing, 0 otherwise
@item PAUSE
pauses the game (a move resumes)
@item GET HEAD X
returns the x pos of the head
@item GET HEAD Y
same with y pos
@item GET FRUIT X
returns the x pos of the current fruit
@item GET FRUIT Y
you guessed it
@item CHECK X Y
returns 1 if (x,y) is occupied by the snake, 0 otherwise
@end ftable

That's all. Check out the example script for an example.


